		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I don't know but I'd double check the initialisation of IRQs at reset. At reset you'd probably want to set the interrupt flag (at least until you actually expect IRQs), write #$00 to $4015 to disable all channels (especially DMC), and read $4015 after that (so it would acknownledge any possible interrupt to be safe).
<br />I know the NES is supposed to disable all sound channels and IRQs when it's soft-resetted, but just to be sure...

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


